txt** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:714): The `MirBorrowckCtxt` structure orchestrates the main borrow checking logic, implementing a `ResultsVisitor` for dataflow results. The `check_access_for_conflict()` method at line 1246 checks if place accesses conflict with existing borrows using `places_conflict` to determine overlaps.\n\n6. **Two-Phase Borrow Resolution**:\n   - Borrow reservation and activation are tracked in `BorrowSet` (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrow_set.rs:16) with activation locations stored in the `activation_map`\n   - The `TwoPhaseActivation` enum at compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrow_set.rs:66 tracks whether a borrow is a two-phase borrow and when it becomes active\n   - The `check_activations()` method at compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:1823 checks whether two-phase borrow activations at a given location conflict with other active borrows\n\nThe complete analysis chain flows from the query entry point through region constraint collection, NLL computation for live ranges, type checking, and finally the per-location borrow checking that uses place conflict detection and manages two-phase borrow activation states."
